The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Monday, April 19, 2004  Calcutta Column

	Dakshineswar temple is frequented by pilgrims and tourists round the year, but the railway station there has remained in an appalling condition. Though a modern ticket counter was recently constructed, the aim of turning it into a model station is yet to be realised. 
	Prahlad Agarwala, Nadia. 
	Vendors selling coconut water are doing brisk business in the sweltering summer. Several pedestrians, too, prefer it to coloured sherbets and soft drinks. But the vendors dump the coconut shells on the pavements. They must not be allowed to operate near bus stands and busy intersections. 
	Debaprasad Mukherjee, Nayapatty Road. 

